entry.tran: 通过投票击败；以多数票击败
entry.def: If you are outvoted, more people vote against what you are suggesting than vote for it, so that your suggestion is defeated.

example.ex: They walked out in protest after being outvoted by the National Salvation Front majority...
example.tran: 他们被救国阵线以多数票否决后，退席以示抗议。

example.ex: Twice his colleagues have outvoted him.
example.tran: 他的同事已经两次否决了他的建议。
